## Overview

Modbus TCP/RTU communication interface for industrial automation devices
such as PLCs, sensors, and actuators. Supports reading and writing holding
registers, input registers, and coils.

## Usage

```python
from {{ interface_name }}_interface import {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface

# Modbus TCP
interface = {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface(host="192.168.1.100", port=502, unit_id=1)
interface.connect()

# Read holding registers
values = interface.read_holding_registers(address=0, count=10)

# Write a single register
interface.write_register(address=0, value=1234)

# Write multiple registers
interface.write_registers(address=10, values=[100, 200, 300])

# Read input registers (read-only sensor data)
inputs = interface.read_input_registers(address=0, count=5)

# Read/write coils (boolean I/O)
coils = interface.read_coils(address=0, count=8)
interface.write_coil(address=0, value=True)

interface.disconnect()
```

