## Dependencies

- `pymodbus>=3.0` for the real interface

## Common Pitfalls

- Modbus register addresses are zero-based in pymodbus but some devices use one-based addressing
- Holding registers store 16-bit unsigned integers (0-65535); use two registers for 32-bit values
- Unit IDs must match the device configuration; default is typically 1
- TCP port 502 is the Modbus standard, but some devices use alternate ports
- RTU mode requires correct baud rate, parity, and stop bit settings to match the device
- Input registers are read-only from the Modbus client perspective
